name: mapreduce.job.running.reduce.limit
description:
The maximum number of simultaneous reduce tasks per job.
  There is no limit if this value is 0 or negative.

name: mapreduce.job.reduces
description:
The default number of reduce tasks per job. Typically set to 99%
  of the cluster's reduce capacity, so that if a node fails the reduces can
  still be executed in a single wave.
  Ignored when mapreduce.framework.name is "local".

name: dfs.content-summary.limit
description:
The maximum content summary counts allowed in one locking period. 0 or a negative number
    means no limit (i.e. no yielding).

name: dfs.client.server-defaults.validity.period.ms
description:
The amount of milliseconds after which cached server defaults are updated.

    By default this parameter is set to 1 hour.
    Support multiple time unit suffix(case insensitive), as described
    in dfs.heartbeat.interval.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.am.container.log.limit.kb
description:
The maximum size of the MRAppMaster attempt container logs in KB.
    0 disables the cap.

name: dfs.batched.ls.limit
description:
Limit the number of paths that can be listed in a single batched
    listing call. printed by ls. If less or equal to
    zero, at most DFS_LIST_LIMIT_DEFAULT (= 1000) will be printed.

name: dfs.stream-buffer-size
description:
The size of buffer to stream files.
  The size of this buffer should probably be a multiple of hardware
  page size (4096 on Intel x86), and it determines how much data is
  buffered during read and write operations.
